        <!-- FAQ -->
        <div class='detail-card fade-in'>
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <div style='margin-top: 16px;'>
            <div class='faq-item active'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>What is the cost of a hair transplant?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>Hair transplant costs vary depending on the technique, number
                  of grafts, and location. On average, FUE procedures range from
                  $2,000 to $15,000. Turkey offers some of the most competitive
                  pricing ($2,500-$5,000), while the US and UK tend to be higher
                  ($8,000-$15,000). We can help you find the best option for
                  your budget.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='faq-item'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>How long does a hair transplant procedure take?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>Most hair transplant procedures take between 6-9 hours,
                  depending on the number of grafts and technique used. FUE
                  typically takes 6-8 hours, while DHI may take 7-9 hours. The
                  procedure is performed under local anesthesia, so you'll be
                  comfortable throughout.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='faq-item'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>What is the recovery time?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>Most patients can return to work within 3-5 days after the
                  procedure. The transplanted area will form small scabs that
                  fall off within 10-14 days. Full results are typically visible
                  after 12-18 months as the transplanted hair grows naturally.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='faq-item'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>What's the difference between FUE and DHI?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>FUE (Follicular Unit Extraction) involves extracting
                  individual follicles and creating channels before implanting
                  them. DHI (Direct Hair Implantation) uses a Choi pen to
                  extract and implant in one step, allowing for more precise
                  angle control and higher density. DHI is generally more
                  expensive but offers slightly faster recovery.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='faq-item'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>Are the results permanent?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>Yes, hair transplant results are permanent. The transplanted
                  hair follicles are taken from the donor area (back and sides
                  of the head), which is genetically resistant to hair loss.
                  These follicles maintain their characteristics even after
                  transplantation, meaning they will continue to grow for a
                  lifetime.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='faq-item'>
              <div class='faq-question'>
                <span>How do I choose the right hospital?</span>
                <span class='faq-toggle'>+</span>
              </div>
              <div class='faq-answer'>
                <p>We recommend considering: the surgeon's experience and
                  qualifications, the clinic's accreditation, before/after
                  results from real patients, patient reviews, the techniques
                  offered, and the overall care package. Our platform verifies
                  all partner hospitals to ensure they meet high standards of
                  quality and safety.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
